and]]'s ''[[Desus & Mero (2016 TV series)|Desus and Mero]]'' and current host of [[Showtime (TV network)|Showtime]]'s ''[[Desus & Mero (2019 TV series)|Desus & Mero]]''<ref name=\"Desus-Mero\">Weiner, Jonah How Desus and Kid Mero Went From Twitter Cranks to Comedy's Hottest Duo Rolling Stone. July 8, 2015</ref>\n* [[The Kid Mero]] (born 1983) \u2013 comedian, former host of [[Viceland]]'s ''[[Desus & Mero (2016 TV series)|Desus and Mero]]'' and current host of [[Showtime (TV network)|Showtime]]'s ''[[Desus & Mero (2019 TV series)|Desus & Mero]]''<ref name=\"Desus-Mero\"/>\n* [[Don Devlin]] (1930\u20132000) \u2013 actor, screenwriter, producer\n* [[Richard Dubin]] (born 1945) \u2013 television writer, director and producer\n* [[Peter Falk]] (1927\u20132011) \u2013 actor<ref>http://www.nycplus.com/nyc18/just79morethings.html</ref>\n* [[Jon Favreau]] (born 1966) \u2013 film and television director and actor<ref>Bowles, Scott (May 7, 2010). \"Favreau's a Comic-Book Hero.\" ''[[USA Today]]''.  pp. 1D-2D.</ref>\n* [[Joe Franklin]] (1926\u20132015) \u2013 TV host of ''Joe Franklin's Memory Lane''<ref name=\"Reeves Wiedeman p. 20\"/>\n* Nick Gee - Legend, Chef\n* [[Cuba Gooding, Jr.]] (born 1968) \u2013 actor\n* [[Howard Gottfried]] (1923\u20132017) -- film producer of academy awarding winning [[Network (1976 film)|Network]] and [[The Hospital]]<ref>Dave Itzkoff, \"Howard Gottfried, 94, Producer of 'Network', Dies. ''New York Times,'' December 17, 2017</ref>\n* Don Gregory (1934\u20132015) \u2013 Broadway theatrical producer<ref>Bruce Weber, \"Don Gregory Dies at 80: Produced Solo Plays.\" ''New York Times'', November 10, 2015</ref>\n* [[Mortimer Halpern]] (1909\u20132006) \u2013 Broadway stage manager\n* [[Jonathan Harris]] (1914\u20132002) \u2013 actor\n* [[Amy Heckerling]] (born 1954) \u2013 film director\n* [[Bernard Herrmann]] (1911\u20131975) \u2013 film composer<ref>\"Bernard Hermann (American Composer), ''Encyclop\u00e6dia Britannica\" \u2013 [http://www.britannica.