tect]], [[landscape architect]] and [[installation artist]]\n* [[Robert Altman (photographer)|Robert Altman]] (born 1944) \u2013 [[photographer]]\n* [[Richard Avedon]] (1923\u20132004) \u2013 photographer\n* [[Alvin Baltrop]] (1948\u20132004) \u2013 photographer\n* [[Margaret Bourke-White]] (1904\u20131971) \u2013 photographer (including [[documentary photography|documentary photographer]])\n* [[Cope2]] (born 1968) \u2013 [[graffiti artist]]\n* [[Willie Cole]] (born 1955) \u2013 artist; uses found material such as his \"America\" blackboard<ref name=\"autogenerated50\">[[Ian Frazier|Frazier, Ian]] (December 21, 2009). \"Dept. of Orientation: El Super\". ''[[The New Yorker]]'', p. 50.</ref>\n* [[Ralph Fasanella]] (1914\u20131997) \u2013 painter\n* [[Ron Galella]] (born 1931) \u2013 [[paparazzi|paparazzo photographer]]<ref>[[Tad Friend|Friend, Tad]] (May 31, 2010). \"Big Game Dept.: No Pictures\".  ''[[The New Yorker]]'', pp. 24\u201325.</ref>\n* [[Horace Ginsbern]] (1902\u20131987) \u2013 architect; designed the landmark [[Art Deco]] [[Park Plaza Apartments (New York)|Park Plaza Apartments]] on [[Jerome Avenue]] in the Bronx, and other New York City structures<ref name=\"nytimes1\">[[Constance Rosenblum|Rosenblum, Constance]] (August 20, 2009). [https://www.nytimes.com/2009/08/21/arts/design/21concourse.html?_r=2&pagewanted=all \"Grand Wasn't It?\"]. ''[[The New York Times]]''.  Retrieved October 29, 2011.</ref>\n* [[Milton Glaser]] (born 1929) \u2013 [[graphic designer]]; designer of the \"[[I Love New York]]\" [[logo]]\n* [[Garry Gross]] (1937\u20132010) \u2013 [[fashion photography|fashion photographer]] (including nude images of [[Brooke Shields]] at age ten), dog [[Portrait photography|portraiture]] photographer and [[dog trainer]]<ref>Hevesi, Dennis (December 7, 2010).[https://www.nytimes.com/2010/12/07/arts/design/07gross.html \"Garry Gross Is Dead at 73; Photographer of Clothes and Their Absence\"]. ''[[The New York Times]]''.  Retrieved October 29, 2011.</re