e-woody.html].</ref>\n* [[June Allyson]] (1917\u20132006) \u2013 actress<ref>Harmetz, Aljean (July 11, 2006). [https://www.nytimes.com/2006/07/11/movies/11allyson.html \"June Allyson, Adoring Wife in MGM Films, Is Dead at 88\"]. ''[[The New York Times]]''. Retrieved November 5, 2007. \"June Allyson was born Ella Geisman on Oct. 7, 1917, in the Bronx.\"</ref>\n* [[Bruce Altman]] (born 1955) \u2013 actor<ref>{{better source|date=August 2013|reason=imdb not generally considered reliable for biographical data (e.g., date/place of birth)}} [https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0022883/]. [[Internet Movie Database]].</ref>\n* [[Christopher Aponte]] \u2013 ballet dancer and choreographer\n* [[Arthur Aviles]] (born 1963) \u2013 dancer and choreographer\n* [[Emanuel Azenberg]] (born 1934) \u2013 theatrical producer\n* [[Lauren Bacall]] (1924\u20132014) \u2013 actress<ref>[http://newyork.cbslocal.com/2014/08/12/cbs-news-actress-lauren-bacall-dies-at-89/]</ref>\n* [[Martin Balsam]] (1919\u20131996) \u2013 film actor\n* [[Anne Bancroft]] (1931\u20132005) \u2013 actress<ref>Berkvist, Robert (June 8, 2005). [https://www.nytimes.com/2005/06/08/movies/08bancroft.html \"Anne Bancroft, Stage and Film Star in Voracious and Vulnerable Roles, Dies at 73\"]. ''[[The New York Times]]''.  Retrieved November 5, 2007. \"Anna Maria Louisa Italiano was born on Sept. 17, 1931, in the Bronx to Italian immigrant parents.\"</ref>\n* [[Ellen Barkin]] (born 1954) \u2013 actress<ref name=\"autogenerated2\">{{cite web|url=http://www.who2.com/city_newyork_thebronx.html |title=Place of Birth Index |publisher=Who2.com |date= |accessdate=March 14, 2011}}</ref>\n* Joseph Bassolino (Joey Boots) (1967\u20132016) \u2013 comedian who popularized the phrase \"Baba Booey\" on the ''Howard Stern Show''<ref>[http://www.cbc.ca/news/entertainment/joey-boots-dead-1.3912324 Associated Press,\"Joey Boots of The Howard Stern Show dead at 49\"]</ref>\n* [[Peter S. Beagle]] (born 1939) \u2013 fantasy and science fiction author\n* 