ometogetherjohn00jonw|author-link=Jon Wiener}}\n* {{cite book|author=Wiener, Jon|year=1999|title=Gimme Some Truth: The John Lennon FBI Files|publisher=[[University of California Press]]|isbn=978-0-520-22246-5|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=FPPj3e_cQIcC&lpg=PP1&pg=PP1#v=onepage|ref=CITEREFWiener1999|accessdate=16 November 2015}}\n* {{cite news|author=Wiener, Jon|work=The Guardian |location=UK|title=He didn't have to do it. That's one reason he's still admired|date=19 December 2006|url=https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2006/dec/19/comment.film|accessdate=18 August 2010|ref=CITEREFWiener2006}}\n{{Refend}}\n\n==Further reading==\n{{refbegin}}\n* [[Larry Kane|Kane, Larry]] (2007). ''[https://archive.org/details/lennonrevealed0000kane Lennon Revealed]''. Running Press. {{ISBN|978-0-7624-2966-0}}\n* {{cite book|first1=Chip|last1=Madinger|first2=Scott|last2=Raile|year=2015|title=Lennonology Strange Days Indeed \u2013 A Scrapbook of Madness|publisher=Open Your Books, LLC|location=Chesterfield, MO|isbn=978-1-63110-175-5|ref=harv}}\n* Pang, May; Edwards, Henry (1983). ''Loving John: The Untold Story''. Warner Books. {{ISBN|0-446-37916-6}}.\n* [[Tim Riley (music critic)|Riley, Tim]] (2011). ''[https://books.google.com/books?id=Pf2YAAAAQBAJ Lennon: Man, Myth, Music]''. Hyperion. {{ISBN|978-1401324520}}\n* Wiener, Jon. [http://www.LennonFBIfiles.com/ The John Lennon FBI Files]\n* Yorke, Richard (1969). [https://web.archive.org/web/20071210181240/http://crawdaddy.wolfgangsvault.com/Article.aspx?id=4372 \"John Lennon: Ringo's Right, We Can't Tour Again\"], ''New Musical Express'', 7 June 1969, reproduced by ''[[Crawdaddy!]]'', 2007.\n* Burger, Jeff, ed: ''Lennon on Lennon: Conversations With John Lennon'' (2017) Chicago Review Press, {{ISBN|978-1-61374-824-4}}\n{{refend}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Wikimedia|collapsible=true|wikt=no}}\n* {{Britannica|335993}}\n* {{allmusic|artist/john-lennon-mn0000232564}}\n* {{HWOF|John Lennon}}\n* {{Rockhall}}\n* {{IMDb name|id=00061